# Windows 11 Installation 
---
>**Note**: This is under the assumption a clean install will be performed without a product key 


## Create Media Creation Tool: 

### Requirements:
- PC / Laptop with reliable internet connection 
- USB Flash Drive (8GB) minimum 
- Product Key (not necessary)

### 1. Download MediaCreationTool.exe 
- From https://www.microsoft.com/en-gb/software-download/windows11 download the Media Creation Tool

### 2. Create Bootable Media 
- Insert the USB drive and ensure it's empty or backup any necessary files as it will be wiped 
- Run the tool and select the USB drive 

### 3. Boot from USB
- Insert USB into the device requiring an OS and boot it up 
>**Note**: If it doesn't load into the Windows Installation Wizard change the boot device in BIOS

### 4. Installation Settings
- Language to install: Set to region specific e.g. English (United Kingdom) 
- Time and currency format: Set to desired region e.g. English (United Kingdom)
- Keyboard Settings: Set to either region specific or keyboard format
>**Note**: For ISO layout keyboard, US input may be preferred
- Setup Option: Install Windows 11 and agree to checkbox
- Product Key: Enter product key or skip if unavailable
- Select Image: Windows 11 Pro
>**Note**: The different editions are for different scenarios, a school may use education while a large organisation may use enterprise
- Agree to terms
- Select location: Disk 0 Unallocated Space
>**Note**: If the device has multiple disks installed they will appear

### 5. Local User Creation 
- Confirm Country/Region and Keyboard layout
- Join via domain to skip Microsoft account login
